    "body": "For some masking operations it's very easy to figure out the shape of the array:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport dask.array as da\r\n\r\na = da.arange(0, 10)\r\n\r\n# shape=(10,):\r\nm = da.ones(10, dtype=bool)\r\na[m] \r\nOut[46]: dask.array<getitem, shape=(nan,), dtype=int32, chunksize=(nan,), chunktype=numpy.ndarray>\r\n\r\n# shape=(10-1,):\r\nm = da.ones(10, dtype=bool)\r\nm[0] = False\r\na[m]\r\nOut[48]: dask.array<getitem, shape=(nan,), dtype=int32, chunksize=(nan,), chunktype=numpy.ndarray>\r\n\r\n# shape=(10-n,):\r\nn = 2\r\nm = da.ones(10, dtype=bool)\r\nm[0:n] = False\r\na[m]\r\nOut[48]: dask.array<getitem, shape=(nan,), dtype=int32, chunksize=(nan,), chunktype=numpy.ndarray>\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot having to do `.compute_chunk_sizes()` after these simple operations seems like a nice feature and will make duck typing with other 3rd party numpy-like packages easier.",
